\pard\intbl\ql
{{\b
Aims of the course: }}\cell\row\pard
}{\trowd\trleft0\trgaph60
\clvertalt\cellx9430
\pard\intbl\ql
{The course introduces modern principles and practices of personnel 
management (human resource management) in the organization, explains 
the key role of personnel management in achieving strategic objectives 
of the organization and introduces fundamental human resource functions 
that determine the competitiveness of the organization in the global 
economy\'2e}\cell\row\pard
}{\trowd\trleft0\trgaph60
\clvertalt\cellx9430
\pard\intbl\ql
{\~}\cell\row\pard
}{\trowd\trleft0\trgaph60
\clvertalt\cellx9430
\pard\intbl\ql
{{\b
Learning outcomes and competences: }}\cell\row\pard
}{\trowd\trleft0\trgaph60
\clvertalt\cellx9430
\pard\intbl\ql
{Upon successful completion of this course, students will be able to:\line
1\'2e Explain the concept and objectives of personnel management in 
the organization; describe the system of human resource functions; 
characterize the role of managers and HR specialists\'2e\line
2\'2e Explain the concept of a job in the organization; characterize 
different approaches to job design; carry out the job analysis; create 
job descriptions\'2e\line
3\'2e Explain the concept and objectives of personnel planning; define 
the process of personnel planing; propose solutions of labour shortage 
or surplus\'2e\line
4\'2e Explain the concept and objectives of employee recruitment and 
selection; characterize different methods of recruitment; formulate 
job advertisement; carry out curriculum vitae analysis and selection 
interview\'2e\line
5\'2e Explain the concept and objectives of employee hiring and orientation; 
define contract of employment; design an orientation program\'2e\line
6\'2e Explain the concept and objectives of performance management; 
characterize different methods of performance appraisal; carry out 
an appraisal interview\'2e\line
7\'2e Explain the concept and objectives of employee training and 
development; identify needs and define plan of training and development; 
characterize different on the job and off the job training and development 
methods; assess results of training and development\'2e\line
8\'2e Explain the concept and objectives of employee compensation; 
characterize different forms of remuneration; describe wage system; 
characterize employee benefits\'2e\line
9\'2e Explain the concept and objectives of working conditions and 
labour relations, particularly organization of working time, creation 
of working environment, safety and health protection, individual and 
collective labour relations\'2e\line
10\'2e Explain the concept and objectives of application of the human 
resource information system, characterize application of information 
and communication technologies in personnel management\'2e }\cell\row\pard
}{\trowd\trleft0\trgaph60
\clvertalt\cellx9430
\pard\intbl\ql
{\~}\cell\row\pard
}{\trowd\trleft0\trgaph60
\clvertalt\cellx9430
\pard\intbl\ql
